
[1]lingering

   LIN'GERING, ppr.

   1. Delaying; loitering.

   2. a. Drawing out in time; remaining long; protracted; as a lingering
   disease.

   To die is the fate of man; but to die with lingering anguish is
   generally his folly.

    LIN'GERING, n. A delaying; a remaining long; tardiness; protraction.

   The lingerings of holyday customs.
